@startuml web-saas
title Department 05 — Web / SaaS ("CareerLens" prototype)

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho

actor "Browser / User" as User

package "FastAPI app (web/app.py)" {
  class WebApp <<FastAPI>> {
    .. pages ..
    GET /
    GET /prototype
    GET /developer/scraping
    GET /build-form
    POST /build
    GET /healthz
    .. auth ..
    GET /api/auth/status
    GET /auth/{provider}/start
    GET /auth/{provider}/callback
    POST /api/auth/disconnect/{provider}
    .. resumes + advisor ..
    GET /api/resumes
    POST /api/cdo/advisor/analyze
    .. social login ..
    POST /api/social-login/{vendor}
    GET /api/social-login/jobs/{job_id}
    POST /api/social-login/{vendor}/disconnect
  }
}

package "Web support modules (web/)" {
  class WebAuthSettings {
    +github / google / microsoft OAuth
    scopes: read:user, user:email
  }
  class CdoAdvisor {
    +analyze(resume) : injection/compliance check
  }
  class MockData <<prototype fixtures>>
  class "templates/ (Jinja2)" as Templates
  class "static/ (CSS/JS)" as Static
}

WebApp --> WebAuthSettings : OAuth flows
WebApp --> CdoAdvisor : /api/cdo/advisor/analyze
WebApp --> MockData : prototype data
WebApp --> Templates : HTML pages
WebApp --> Static : assets

User --> WebApp : HTTP

' --- wraps the core ---
WebApp ..> "Dept 01: Pipeline.run()" : POST /build
WebApp ..> "Dept 02: social-login\n(browser_login / auth)" : POST /api/social-login

note bottom of WebApp
  Prototype layer. Wraps the CLI pipeline
  behind a UI. OAuth here is for IDENTITY
  (read:user, user:email) — used to pre-fill
  social login, not to act on the user's behalf.
  NOT YET: user DB, billing, rate limiting.
end note
@enduml
